<p>I have two classes Bar and Foo</p>  <pre><code>class Bar {   Foo attr;         public:         Bar(int i); }  class Foo {   std::string _name;         public:         Foo(std::string name) : _name(name){} } </code></pre>  <p>The problem is that <code>Foo</code>has no default constructor but only one constructor that takes a <code>std::string</code>. moreover <code>operator=</code> is a private member of Foo. So how can I initialize <code>attr</code> so that its name will be <code>"good"</code> if <code>i==0</code> and <code>"bad"</code> otherwise.</p>